    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP" source="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/LHNEVHEN">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"  style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>Ͱε̄γέ̄σιπός ἐ̄μ
                    <lb n="2"  style="text-direction:l-to-r"/>ι τὺ Βύλιος
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
               <listApp><app><note>Text of Boffa</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>I am Hegesipos, (son) of Bulis</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" source="https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/LHNEVHEN">
                <p>Hegesippos sono, (figlio) di Bulis</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>A number of other uninscribed stele have been found in the necropolis, but this is the only funerary inscription from ancient Mylai to date, and parallels in the Euboean alphabet in the region are rare.</p>
            </div>
